cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on 3D shape retrieval, which involves analyzing and comparing shapes in a high-dimensional space. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), as well as graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper proposes a novel metric loss for learning discriminative shape representations, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on two popular 3D object retrieval benchmarks, which is a common practice in computer vision and multimedia research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, and cs.MM.
